ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would summarize it as a survey course. I would recommend it to other graduate students that do not have a background in the study of ceramic assemblages.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Ceramic analysis is a subject that I had not been exposed to during my undergraduate career when I focused on geological and geographical applications in archaeology. For my thesis this year, I was thrown into the field of ceramics with very little prior knowledge. This class helped give me a sturdy foundation on which to build my thesis and the techniques and information that I learned in this class will carry over into my research on a regular basis.
